<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She is currently acting as the Jury President for the 77th annual Venice Film Festival.</p>

<p>And Cate Blanchett looked effortlessly stylish in a red jumpsuit as he hopped onto a boat after leaving the Excelsior Hotel for another packed day at the event on Friday.</p>

<p>The Thor: Ragnarok star, 51, looked every inch the star in the crimson number which featured button detailing and was cinched in at the waist.</p>

<p>Star: Cate Blanchett looked effortlessly stylish in a red jumpsuit as she hopped on board a boat at the 77th Venice Film Festival on Friday</p>

<p>Stylish: The Thor: Ragnarok star, 51, looked every inch the star in the crimson number which featured button detailing and was cinched in at the waist</p>

<p>The blonde beauty teamed the jumpsuit with a white over-the-shoulder bag, gold sunglasses and an array of glitzy accessories including a gold bracelet. </p>

<p>Cate made sure to put safety first for her outing in the Italian city by donning a face mask and wore her light tresses in her trademark chic bob. </p>

<p>She was surrounded by her entourage as she was helped onto the boat after leaving the hotel before cruising away down the canal.  </p>

<p>Precautions: Cate made sure to put safety first for her outing in the Italian city and wore her light tresses in her trademark chic bob</p>

<p>Glam: The blonde beauty teamed the jumpsuit with a white over-the-shoulder bag, gold sunglasses and an array of glitzy accessories including a gold bracelet</p>

<p>Helping hand: She was surrounded by her entourage as she was helped onto the boat after leaving the hotel</p>

<p>Boat trip: Cate looked relaxed as she made her way onto the boat before cruising off down the canal</p>

<p>Cropped do: Cate wore her hair in a blonde bob and opted for natural makeup for the outing on Friday </p>

<p>Duo: Cate was joined by Alberto Barbera, the Director of the 77th Venice International Film Festival and other Jury members</p>

<p>Cate is heading the jury at Venice during an historic year, when the number of women directors competing for the top prize has quadrupled to eight.</p>

<p>'I think a good performance is a good performance no matter the sexual orientation of who is making them,' she added of her thoughts on the matter.</p>

<p>'The hardest thing as a jury member is to sit in judgement of other people's work. That's the hardest thing not the (gender) demarcation.'  </p>

<p>Classy: Cate exuded sophistication in the jumpsuit which had brown buttons down the front</p>

<p>In charge: Cate is heading the jury at Venice during an historic year, when the number of women directors competing for the top prize has quadrupled to eight</p>

<p>Trip out: Cate gazed out at the beautiful views of Venice during the boat trip on Friday morning</p>

<p>Mask: She wore a blue face covering for the trip out where she was accompanied by her team</p>

<p>Cate's recently revealed she prefers to be referred to as an actor than an actress, as she often found the latter term to be used in a 'pejorative sense'. </p>

<p>Throwing her support behind Berlin International Film Festival's new plan to do away with gendered awards, she told AFP: 'I have always referred to myself as an actor. </p>

<p>'I am of the generation where the word actress was used almost always in a pejorative sense. So I claim the other space.' </p>

<p>Stepping out: Cate was spotted leaving the Excelsior Hotel during the 77th Venice Film Festival on Friday</p>

<p>Cruising: The boat set off along the canal after Cate and her entourage were safely on board</p>

<p>Trip out: Cate looked gorgeous in the red jumpsuit as she stepped out on Friday morning </p>
